<br>
I did not test the FT because a FT of one is time consuming to test and unless you are prefect in your method, questionable.  {The best way is to cast with a large spell, then a small spell, and then your smallest fastest spell to get as much as possible out of mana.  Then count how many tics til you can cast a know mana spell {lets call this spell B}.  You should have a standing regen of 1 + 1 FT.  After casting the last smallest fastest spell, you will be 0 to (mana cost of that spell -1) + 1 (2 if the FT works) per 6 second tic border you cross {a 5 second spell could be 0 or 1}.  As you can see, there is a lot of variance in how much mana you start with win it is &quot;0&quot;.  A larger mana cast for spell A will help make this variance noise, but the larger the mana, the longer it takes to med.  <br>
